The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index fell 0.2 percent to 36,499.85.  Grupo Aeroportuario del Sureste SAB (ASURB MM), the
operator of airports in southern Mexico, climbed 1 percent to
69.45 pesos. Lower  oil prices  signal reduced fuel costs that can
spur air travel. Twenty of 39 analysts, or 51 percent, forecast
oil will drop next week, according to a Bloomberg News survey.
Thirteen respondents, or 33 percent, predicted prices will
increase and six estimated there will be little change.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES* MM), Mexicoâ€™s largest
silver producer, advanced 1.6 percent to 449.18 pesos. Silver
futures for September delivery rose as much as 1 percent to
$36.895 an ounce on the Comex in  New York .  To contact the reporter on this story:
